1{-# LANGUAGE FlexibleInstances #-}
2{-# LANGUAGE MultiParamTypeClasses #-}
3{-# OPTIONS_GHC -Wall #-}
4
5-- | Parser for token tree.
6
7module Koshucode.Baala.Syntax.Tree.Parse
8  ( -- * Type
9    Tree, TTree, NamedTrees,
10
11    -- * Parser
12    ToTrees (..),
13    ttreeGroup,
14    withTrees,
15    readClauseTrees,
16  ) where
17
18import qualified Koshucode.Baala.Overture                as O
19import qualified Koshucode.Baala.Base                    as B
20import qualified Koshucode.Baala.Syntax.Symbol           as S
21import qualified Koshucode.Baala.Syntax.Token            as S
22import qualified Koshucode.Baala.Syntax.Tree.Bracket     as S
23
24
25-- --------------------------------------------  Type
26
27-- | Tree of tokens.
28type Tree = TTree String
29
30-- | Tree of tokens.
31type TTree t = B.CodeTree S.BracketType S.TToken t
32
33-- | Pair of token trees and its name.
34type NamedTrees = B.Named [Tree]
35
36-- | Wrap trees in group.
37ttreeGroup :: [TTree t] -> TTree t
38ttreeGroup = B.codeTreeWrap S.BracketGroup
39
40
41-- --------------------------------------------  Parser
42
43-- | Convert to token trees.
44class ToTrees t a where
45    -- | Convert to list of token trees.
46    toTrees :: (O.Textual t, S.ToTermName t) => a -> B.Ab [TTree t]
47
48    -- | Convert to token tree.
49    toTree :: (O.Textual t, S.ToTermName t) => a -> B.Ab (TTree t)
50    toTree a = ttreeGroup <$> toTrees a
51
52    -- | List of token trees or error.
53    toTrees' :: (O.Textual t, S.ToTermName t) => a -> [TTree t]
54    toTrees' = B.unabort . toTrees
55
56    -- | Token tree or error.
57    toTree' :: (O.Textual t, S.ToTermName t) => a -> TTree t
58    toTree' = B.unabort . toTree
59
60instance ToTrees t String where
61    toTrees = tokenTrees . S.toks
62
63instance ToTrees t B.Tx where
64    toTrees = toTrees . B.txString
65
66instance ToTrees t B.Tz where
67    toTrees = toTrees . B.tzString
68
69instance ToTrees t O.Bz where
70    toTrees = toTrees . B.bzString
71
72instance ToTrees t O.Bs where
73    toTrees = toTrees . B.bsString
74
75instance ToTrees t [S.TToken t] where
76    toTrees = tokenTrees
77
78instance ToTrees t [TTree t] where
79    toTrees = Right
80
81instance ToTrees t (S.TokenClause t) where
82    toTrees = toTrees . B.clauseTokens
83
84-- | Parse tokens with brackets into trees.
85--   Blank tokens and comments are excluded.
86tokenTrees :: (O.Textual t, B.IsString t) => [S.TToken t] -> B.Ab [TTree t]
87tokenTrees = B.codeTrees S.getBracketType B.BracketNone . S.prepareTokens
88
89-- | Call function with token trees.
90--
91--   >>> withTrees Right "a"
92--   Right [TreeL (TText /0.1.0/ TextRaw "a")]
93--
94withTrees :: (O.Textual t, S.ToTermName t, ToTrees t a) => ([TTree t] -> B.Ab b) -> a -> B.Ab b
95withTrees f a = f O.# toTrees a
96
97-- | Read clauses and convert to token trees.
98readClauseTrees :: FilePath -> B.IOAb [[TTree String]]
99readClauseTrees path =
100    do ls' <- S.readClauses path
101       return $ case ls' :: B.Ab [S.TokenClause String] of
102         Right ls   -> toTrees O.<#> ls
103         Left a     -> Left a
104
